## Component Composition

### Snippets replace slots

Svelte 5 removes `<slot>`. Use `{#snippet}` and `{@render}` instead.

**Declaring a snippet (local):**

```svelte
{#snippet row(item)}
  <li>{item.name}</li>
{/snippet}

{@render row(selectedItem)}
```

**Accepting children (implicit snippet):**

```svelte
<!-- Parent -->
<Card>
  <p>Hello</p>
</Card>

<!-- Card.svelte -->
<script lang="ts">
  import type { Snippet } from 'svelte';
  let { children }: { children: Snippet } = $props();
</script>

<div class="card">
  {@render children()}
</div>
```

**Named snippets (replace named slots):**

```svelte
<!-- Parent -->
<Card>
  {#snippet header()}
    <h2>Title</h2>
  {/snippet}
  <p>Body content as children.</p>
</Card>

<!-- Card.svelte -->
<script lang="ts">
  import type { Snippet } from 'svelte';
  let {
    header,
    children
  }: {
    header?: Snippet;
    children: Snippet;
  } = $props();
</script>

<div>
  {#if header}{@render header()}{/if}
  {@render children()}
</div>
```

**Typed snippet with parameters:**

```svelte
<script lang="ts">
  import type { Snippet } from 'svelte';
  let {
    row
  }: {
    row: Snippet<[item: { name: string; id: number }]>;
  } = $props();
</script>
```

### Events — use callback props

Svelte 5 removes `createEventDispatcher`. Pass callback functions as props instead.

```svelte
<!-- Child -->
<script lang="ts">
  let { onclick }: { onclick?: (detail: string) => void } = $props();
</script>
<button onclick={() => onclick?.('clicked')}>Click</button>

<!-- Parent -->
<Child onclick={(detail) => console.log(detail)} />
```

- For DOM events, use the lowercase attribute directly: `onclick`, `oninput`, `onkeydown`, etc.
- NEVER use `on:click` colon syntax — it is removed in Svelte 5.
- NEVER use `createEventDispatcher`.

