## Shared Reactive State (replacing stores)

Instead of Svelte stores, export reactive state from `.svelte.ts` files:

```ts
// counter.svelte.ts
let count = $state(0);

export function increment() {
  count++;
}

export function getCount() {
  return count;
}
```

- File MUST use `.svelte.ts` extension so the compiler processes runes.
- Prefer exporting getter functions or using `$derived` for read access to keep reactivity intact when consumed across components.

---

## Quick Reference

```
$state(value)          → mutable reactive state
$state.raw(value)      → reactive (reassign only, no deep tracking)
$derived(expr)         → computed from reactive values
$derived.by(() => {})  → multi-statement computed
$effect(() => {})      → side effect (runs after DOM update)
$effect.pre(() => {})  → side effect (runs before DOM update)
$props()               → component inputs (replaces export let)
$bindable(default)     → marks a prop as two-way bindable
$inspect(value)        → dev-only console logging
{#snippet name()}      → define a reusable template block
{@render name()}       → render a snippet
```
